post_text: Youth Baseball/Softball registrations for our spring/summer leagues are currently taking place at the Greeneville Parks and Recreation. Registrants must turn 5 before May 1, 2019 and can not turn 17 before May 1, 2019. There is a $10.00 registration fee for each player (if more than 2 in a household, then the 3rd player is only 5.00). Deadline is Friday, March 15, 2019. If anyone has any questions, please call 638-3194 or 638-3144.

post_text:
CDHS Art Students Put New Twist on Canvas!

Here's the challenge for high-school art students. Take a blank pair of Vans shoes and create something. Anything. Go wild.
The goal is to win a trip to Vans headquarters, where the top five finalists will present their projects and vie for the grand prize.

In its eighth annual Vans Custom Culture art competition, the Los Angeles shoe maker is asking high-school art teachers to sign up their classes in a competition to create the most artistic and inventive designs using blank Vans shoes as their canvas.
The grand prize is $50,000 towards the winning school's arts program. The four runner-up schools will each be rewarded $4,000.

post_text: Dr. Candice McQueen, Tennessee’s Commissioner of Education, took time to visit Ottway Elementary yesterday. Representative David Hawk, Senator Steve Southerland, and Central Office staff joined her there for classroom visits. Along with talking to students, Dr. McQueen also took time to get feedback from teachers about curriculum and the new TNReady assessments.
